System usefulness is critical to voluntary use of a new system [21], [22], and generally refers to the extent to which an individual considers a system useful in his or her work role. BioPortal offers effective data integration support, and has sophisticated built-in functionalities and intuitive visualization designs; as a result, it can be expected to better support the demanding information processing often required in an analysis task. Hence, we tested the following hypothesis. \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
